******
[1] Egypt (Beni Suef)
Date: Mon 15 Dec 2014
From: Abdallah Samy <samyasu@aol.com> [edited]


New measles cases have been reported in different areas of Egypt. For a few weeks, all measles cases were only reported in Marsa Matrouh province. Most of these cases were identified from Siwa Oasis.

Yesterday [14 Dec 2014], the disease appeared in another area, where a child died from measles in Beni Suef Province. The cases are still underestimated, but they should raise an alarm, with high risks of contracting measles now in Egypt.

The Ministry of Health regulations should be offered to people through local mass media, especially in infected areas, and give information on how they can report symptoms as soon as possible to the health authorities.

--
Abdallah Samy
Ain Shams University & the University of Kansas
<samyasu@aol.com>

