[2] South Africa (7 provinces)
Date: Mon 15 De 2014
Source: Times Live, Reuters [edited]
http://www.timeslive.co.za/thetimes/2014/12/15/no-crisis-as-measles-outbreak-hits-7-provinces


7 provinces have reported outbreaks of measles, but the Health Department does not regard the resurgence as a crisis.

1st reports said the outbreaks were in Gauteng, Mpumalanga, KwaZulu-Natal, Northern Cape and Western Cape. But now the National Institute for Communicable Diseases says there has been an increase in laboratory-confirmed measles cases in 2 more provinces, Eastern Cape and Free State. Institute spokesman Nombuso Shabalala said: "Measles vaccines are safe and highly effective at preventing it."

The Gauteng health department urged parents to take children to the nearest clinic for a measles vaccination. It said it had introduced a campaign to vaccinate children between 6 months and 15 years. Spokesman Prince Hamnca said: "During the festive season, the movement of people will pose a risk to the containment and prevention of the disease. It's for this reason that the department urges all parents to ensure that their children are vaccinated."

National Health Department spokesman Popo Maja said it was worried about the current outbreak, "but it is not a crisis. The national institute is monitoring the situation and advising us."

[Byline: David Mercado]

